revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tpPolicyTable.name: tpPolicyTable
tpPolicyTable.description: A list of policy entries. Here you can add ACLs and create corresponding actions for the policy.

tpPolicyEntry.name: tpPolicyEntry
tpPolicyEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of policy.

tpMirrorPort.name: tpMirrorPort
tpMirrorPort.description: mirror the data packets in the policy to the specific port. if traffic mirror doesnt work, please set it to 0

tpConditionRate.name: tpConditionRate
tpConditionRate.description: limit the transmission rate of the data packets in the policy.(1-1000000Kbps), if traffic condition doesnt work, please set it to 0

tpIfExceedOperation.name: tpIfExceedOperation
tpIfExceedOperation.description: Specify the disposal way of the data packets those are transmitted beyond the rate. (you must set the conditionRate firstly)

tpRedirectPort.name: tpRedirectPort
tpRedirectPort.description: Forward the data packets those match the corresponding ACL to the specific port, if you want redirect to vlan, please set it to 0

tpQosRemarkDSCP.name: tpQosRemarkDSCP
tpQosRemarkDSCP.description: Specify the DSCP region for the data packets those match the corresponding ACL.

tpQosRemarkLocalPri.name: tpQosRemarkLocalPri
tpQosRemarkLocalPri.description: Specify the local priority for the data packets those match the corresponding ACL.

tpPolicyStatus.name: tpPolicyStatus
tpPolicyStatus.description: the following two values are states: these values may be read or written active(1), notInService(2), the following value is a state: this value may be read, but not written notReady(3), the following three values are actions: these values may be written, but are never read createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5), destroy(6)

tpPolicyBindPortTable.name: tpPolicyBindPortTable
tpPolicyBindPortTable.description: A list of policy port binding entries. Here you can bind a policy to a port.

tpPolicyBindPortEntry.name: tpPolicyBindPortEntry
tpPolicyBindPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of policy port binding.

tpBindPortPolicyName.name: tpBindPortPolicyName
tpBindPortPolicyName.description: The name of the policy you want to bind.(the policy name must be existent)

tpPolicyPort.name: tpPolicyPort
tpPolicyPort.description: The port that the policy bind to

tpPolicyBindPortStatus.name: tpPolicyBindPortStatus

tpPolicyVlan.name: tpPolicyVlan
